fields.description: The Fender Ritchie Blackmore Stratocaster® Electric Guitar, Olympic White is a Ritchie Blackmore signature guitar based on Blackmore’s favourite ’70s model.

The Fender Player Precision Bass MN (3-Colour Sunburst) offers authentic Precision Bass feeling at a particularly attractive price. This electric instrument has a classic Alder body and a bolt-on Maple neck in the comfortable "Modern C" profile, with the typical 41.3mm nut width, providing enough space for clean fingering of the 20x fret Maple fingerboard.

The Fender FA-125CE Natural acoustic guitar is perfect for beginners, or advanced guitarists thanks to its excellent functionality and quality craftsmanship. The large dreadnought body also produces a powerful sound that is perfect for expressive strumming and vocal accompaniment. A generous cutaway also facilitates access to the high frets and gives the instrument a very modern appearance.

The Yamaha SLG 200 Silent Guitar N is a nylon guitar powered by an SRT undersaddle pickup capturing and making the most of individual string vibrations.

Inspired by traditional classical guitar design, the SLG200N features a slim neck, thin body, and low action that lets players adopt a more aggressive style, allowing even those players who wouldn't normally choose to perform with a classical guitar to play it with ease.

The Wildkat is one of the classics of the Epiphone line-up. The instrument, which has been built since the 1930s, presents itself as a versatile semi-hollow with an arched top made from Flamed Maple with a Mahogany body. In addition to the body, two P-90R and P-90T pickups with traditional Dogears are responsible for providing a clear and defined sound image with sufficient treble and high mids.

The Gibson Thunderbird Bass Ebony is a genuine rock bass that picks up on the distinctive reverse design and also impresses with its solid sound and high playing comfort. The heart of the four-string instrument is the nine-piece neck made of mahogany and walnut, which in combination with the body wings made of mahogany promises a sustain-strong sound. The slim "Rounded" neck profile with 38 mm saddle width also offers manoeuvrable playing characteristics, so that every groove goes off by itself.

The Fender Player Jazz Bass MN (Polar White) offers the authentic Jazz Bass feeling with playing comfort and a wide range of Bass sounds for almost any musical environment. Fender relies on the proven off-set design with Alder body and screwed Maple neck, which, thanks to the "Modern C" profile with 38mm saddle width, offers optimum conditions for extremely smooth playability.

With the ' Gibson 60s Les Paul Standard Tribute Bourbon Burst , the Original Collection presents Gibson USA an electric guitar that authentically captures the spirit and sound of the innovative Singlecut models from the early 1960s. Accordingly, the Gibson '60s Les Paul Standard has a massive mahogany body without weight relief and a curly maple top in superior AA quality.

The Fender Squier Mini Precision Bass IL Black is a handy electric short-scale bass that combines the typical Precision style with the comfortable playability of a shortened scale length and is therefore the ideal instrument for beginners or comfort seeking bassists. In addition to the poplar body in classic P-Bass style, Squier uses a bolt-on maple neck with Laurel fretboard for the construction of the Mini Precision Bass.
